1 AN ACT relating to the mental health of first responders.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 95A.292 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) The commission shall establish the Alan "Chip" Terry Professional Development
5 and Wellness Program for firefighters and rescue squad members.
6 (2) As used in this section, "rescue squad member" means an individual who is a
7 member of a rescue squad as defined in KRS 39F.010.
8 (3) The program shall:
9 (a) Use seminar-based peer support and counseling services designed to reduce
10 negative mental and behavioral health outcomes; and
11 (b) Be offered to Kentucky professional and volunteer firefighters and rescue
12 squad members in Kentucky at least two (2) times each calendar year.
13 (4)[(3)] On a limited basis, the program may be offered to professional and volunteer
14 firefighters and rescue squad members from states other than Kentucky upon
15 application to and approval by the executive director. However, no Kentucky
16 professional and volunteer firefighters or rescue squad members may be denied
17 admission to the program if professional and volunteer firefighters or rescue squad
18 members from another state are admitted to the program.
19 (5)[(4)] The commission shall promulgate administrative regulations in accordance
20 with KRS Chapter 13A to implement this section. The administrative regulations
21 shall address, at a minimum:
22 (a) The required qualifications and duties of any person used by the commission
23 to implement or administer the program;
24 (b) The curriculum, programming, seminar type, and treatment modalities used in
25 the program;
26 (c) The extent to which a participating firefighter or rescue squad member's
27 [firefighter's ]relatives or friends may participate in seminars;
