7 (6)[(5)] The commission shall enter into an agreement with the Division of
8 Emergency Management to provide rescue squad members with access to the
9 program.
10 (7) (a) Except as provided in paragraphs (b) and (c) of this subsection,
11 communications, identifying data, and any reports made in the application for
12 or in the course of a firefighter or rescue squad member's[ firefighter's]
13 participation in the program shall be confidential and privileged from
14 disclosure in any civil or criminal proceeding and shall not be subject to
15 discovery, disclosure, or production upon the order or subpoena of a court or
16 other agency with subpoena power, regardless of who possesses them. The
17 participating firefighter or rescue squad member is the holder of the
18 privilege.
19 (b) The commission may use anonymous data for research, statistical analysis,
20 and educational purposes.
21 (c) Any communication making an actual threat of physical violence against a
22 clearly identified or reasonably identifiable victim or an actual threat of some
23 specific violent act may be revealed by the program in order to prevent the
24 commission of any physical violence or violent act using the protocol
25 established in KRS 202A.400.
