15 (9)[(7)] (a) For the purposes of this subsection, "critical incident" means any event
16 that has a stressful impact sufficient enough to overwhelm a firefighter or
17 rescue squad member's[ firefighter's] usual coping strategies. These events
18 may include:
19 1. A fire or vehicle crash resulting in serious injury or death to a first
20 responder or citizen;
21 2. A firefighter or rescue squad member being the victim of a felonious
22 assault;
23 3. The death of a colleague or partner;
24 4. A death of, or serious injury to, a person in the medical care of the
25 firefighter or rescue squad member;
26 5. The severe injury to, or death of, a child, particularly if the firefighter or
27 rescue squad member has a child of or near the same age; or
